{{Refimprove|date=October 2017}} '''Lake Malawi Museum''' is a museum on [[Lake Malawi]] in [[Malawi]]. Situated in the Old Gymkhana Club and organized by the Society of Malawi since 1971<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.visitmalawi.mw/index.php/component/k2/item/122-lake-malawi-in-mangochi |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-11-22 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129032013/http://www.visitmalawi.mw/index.php/component/k2/item/122-lake-malawi-in-mangochi |archivedate=2014-11-29 |df= }} </ref> (and likely not updated since then), the museum is located near the Queen Victoria memorial near the [[Bakili Muluzi]] Bridge in [[Mangochi]] town, [[Mangochi District]], within the [[Southern Region, Malawi|Southern Region]] of Malawi.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://mw.geoview.info/lake_malawi_museum,902487985n | title=Lake Malawi Museum | website=Geoview.info| accessdate=8 August 2014 }}</ref>
